
<p>CNBC:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>President Donald Trump on Monday delayed high U.S. tariffs on
Chinese goods from snapping back into place for another 90 days, a
White House official told CNBC. [...]</p>

<p>Monday’s extension is the latest example of how Trump’s on-again,
off-again tariffs have shifted with little prior notice, a dynamic
that has made U.S. trade policy unpredictable for many businesses.</p>
</blockquote>

<p><a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/07/22/1256040785/trump-taco-wall-street-stock-market-tariffs">TACO</a> Tuesday, but on a Monday. What a country! America really is great again.</p>

<p>Bonus question for the CNBC copy desk: how much water is the word <em>many</em> carrying in that closing sentence?</p>

